casebody.data:
Elisabeth WEBB
v.
Daniel Andrew WEBB NO. 2018-C-0320 Supreme Court of Louisiana. April 27, 2018

On Writ of Certiorari and/or Review Twenty-Fourth Judicial District Court, Parish of Jefferson, No. 712-074, Division N; Court of Appeal, Fifth Circuit, No. 16-CA-567.

*114And, whereas, the Court has this date, pursuant to Article 5, Section 5, of the Constitution of Louisiana, made and issued the following order, to wit-"It is ordered that the writ of review issue; that the District Court and the Court of Appeal send up the record in Duplicate of the case; and that counsel for all parties be notified."

Now, therefore, the said District Court and the Court of Appeal is hereby commanded, in the name of the State of Louisiana and of this Honorable Court, to send up forthwith to this Court, in accordance with Supreme Court Rule 1, at the City of New Orleans, the record in duplicate of the above-entitled case.
